<DIV>/target &lt;MA NAME HERE&gt;</DIV>
<DIV>/cast 5</DIV>
<DIV>/cast 5</DIV>
<DIV>/cast 5</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>If it goes off on the first time, I get you cannot use this command while casting a spell twice, no biggie...&nbsp; If it fizzles the first time, the second time picks it up, etc...&nbsp; You cannot do this with a bard as the first /cast would start the song and the second /cast would end it, and the third /cast would start it again...&nbsp; So we cannot use hotkeys effectively for twisting, as other casters can for their spells...&nbsp; With the /stopsong command I see no reason why hitting the gem a second time or using a /cast command again should stop the song.&nbsp; </DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>My assumption is this is a way for SOE to control how powerful bards are, just my .02...&nbsp; I would LOVE to see our songs act as spells where hitting the gem again would give a "you cannot use that command while casting a spell" thing...&nbsp; Would make hotkeys work MUCH smoother...</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>Ohh well, just my opinion..&nbsp; I don't agree with third party macro programs, I consider them cheating..&nbsp; But Gamepads are a great way to play more comfortably...</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>so please please please, make our song gems respond the same as spell gems 8)</DIV>
