			<td colspan=2 class="msg_text_cell" width="100%" valign=top style="text-align: justify; " >
												<DIV></DIV>
<DIV></DIV>
<DIV></DIV>
<DIV></DIV>
<DIV></DIV>
<P>I seldom post to any boards as a general rule. This thread interest me because my wife plays a bard and complains about wrist pains in relation to twisting. I am disappointed somewhat that although the community answer to this issue is fairly clear,&nbsp;only&nbsp;one reply from the developer appears. That reply was to deny a statement. How about an acknowledgement to the community that the 2 main suggested fix concepts&nbsp;are being examined. My wifes wrists hurt, she is a strong candidate to develop arthritis and <STRONG>carpal</STRONG> <B>tunnel</B> from her&nbsp;family already. I do not want her love of the bard to accelerate&nbsp;these conditions any faster than is absolutely necessary. I do not support any 3rd party programs that affect a parent program. I insist the parent program make it so such workarounds are not nessasary. I&nbsp;personaly do not know anyone with physical disabilities who play this game. I have not seen any strong movement by those with disabilities toward making specific changes to the game to promote playability by the&nbsp;disabled. I do know that if my wife ever sheds a single tear of pain because of her conditions and EQ, I'll encourage her to stop play, or at least stop playing a bard. Bards are the most key-tapping intensive character class there is, in my opinion. For the chat side of it we all seem to agree. It is a widely accepted fate of bards that while in performance mode chat is not easily accomplished and better off left alone. A bard trying to communicate while performing can get both bards and whole parties wiped.</P>
<P>Thanks for your time spent reading my thoughts;</P>
<P>Felon - 61 Beastlord - Lany</P>
																		
