			<td colspan=2 class="msg_text_cell" width="100%" valign=top style="text-align: justify; " >
												<DIV>I never have wrist problems because of twisting, mainly because my FINGERS are doing all the work, not the wrist..</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>I never twist more than 4 songs/melee, so it's somewhat easy to keep two fingers occupied for the task and have all the casual songs in slots 1-3 on pages 1and2 of hotkeys.</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>BUT, I do agree something should be made.. I dont know, some auto-twist thingie.. I'm known to be very quiet, because simply.. If you twist, you can talk only for 2.9seconds in between a single twist.. which means you have to type very fast.. combined with movng around and positioning on melee, that can be quite hazardous.</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>It's simple.</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>If bard is talking they arent twisting. If they arent twisting, we might as well be rangers.</DIV>
