												<DIV></DIV><STRONG></STRONG>
<DIV></DIV>
<DIV>Your fingers are connected to your wrists.&nbsp; Using your fingers uses your wrists.&nbsp; Long term, repetitive key-strokes with your <EM>fingers</EM> can lead to problems with your <EM>wrists</EM>.&nbsp; There is no doubt in my mind what-so-ever that full-time EQ players,&nbsp;who play bards,&nbsp;run a <STRONG>much higher risk</STRONG> for serious long term problems such as carpal tunnel.&nbsp; Especially if their job also requires repetitive hand/finger/wrist activity.</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>My wife switched to playing her bard full-time.&nbsp; I bought her a Nostromo n52 and we&nbsp;like it very much.&nbsp; Yes, it takes some of the skill out of playing a bard, but no video game is worth permanent physical injury IMO.</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
